From: DevBox UML arm64 Port
Subject: [PATCH 10/13] arm64/um: full signal.c — setup_signal_stack_si + rt_sigreturn

Complete rewrite of arch/arm64/um/signal.c.

The previous stub only had the skeleton. This implements the full
arm64 rt_sigframe layout matching what native arm64 glibc/kernel uses:

  struct rt_sigframe {
      struct siginfo info;
      struct ucontext uc;      // contains struct sigcontext with regs+FP
  };

Key design choices for UML:
- FP/SIMD state saved inline in sigcontext.__reserved[] as fpsimd_context.
  We write the fpsimd_context header (magic + size) so that glibc's
  unwinder and libgcc's _Unwind_Resume can find and restore FP state.
- pretcode not needed on arm64: SA_RESTORER is always set (glibc sets it);
  the restorer calls __NR_rt_sigreturn directly.
- sp must be 16-byte aligned before the call instruction on arm64 AAPCS64.

diff --git a/arch/arm64/um/signal.c b/arch/arm64/um/signal.c
--- a/arch/arm64/um/signal.c
+++ b/arch/arm64/um/signal.c
@@ -1,78 +1,221 @@
